04/08/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Two bombs exploded within ten minutes of each other in southern Turkey on Friday (4 August), injuring as many as ten people.
The first bomb went off in front of a bank on a busy road in the southern city of Adana.
An official say the second occurred some 30m away, at a construction site, after police and journalists had rushed to the scene of the first blast.
(AP - 04/08/06)
